An escaping `--include` is rejected with a rackabel three-part frame (RK4004) BEFORE
any build runs — the include guard is a pre-flight validation gate (DESIGN §2 pack).
The frame is written to stderr; trycmd matches it here, and the exit code is the
validation code 4.

```
$ rackabel pack -i ../outside.txt
? 4
error: an --include path must stay inside the extension directory [RK4004]
  --> --include ../outside.txt
  help: remove the `..` segments — only files within the project can be bundled
(run `rackabel explain RK4004` for details)

```

An absolute `--include` is likewise a validation failure (exit 4).

```
$ rackabel pack --include /tmp/escape.txt
? 4
error: an --include path must be relative to the extension directory [RK4004]
  --> --include /tmp/escape.txt
  help: use a path relative to the project root, e.g. `-i assets/icon.png`
(run `rackabel explain RK4004` for details)

```
